<h2 id="the-wal-protocol--new">The WAL Protocol ‚≠ź NEW</h2>

<p><strong>The Law:</strong> You are a stateful operator. Chat history is a BUFFER, not storage. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">SESSION-STATE.md</code> is your ‚ÄúRAM‚ÄĚ ‚ÄĒ the ONLY place specific details are safe.</p>

<h3 id="trigger--scan-every-message-for">Trigger ‚ÄĒ SCAN EVERY MESSAGE FOR:</h3>

<ul>
  <li>‚úŹÔłŹ <strong>Corrections</strong> ‚ÄĒ ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs X, not Y‚ÄĚ / ‚ÄúActually‚Ä¶‚ÄĚ / ‚ÄúNo, I meant‚Ä¶‚ÄĚ</li>
  <li>ūüďć <strong>Proper nouns</strong> ‚ÄĒ Names, places, companies, products</li>
  <li>ūüé® <strong>Preferences</strong> ‚ÄĒ Colors, styles, approaches, ‚ÄúI like/don‚Äôt like‚ÄĚ</li>
  <li>ūüďč <strong>Decisions</strong> ‚ÄĒ ‚ÄúLet‚Äôs do X‚ÄĚ / ‚ÄúGo with Y‚ÄĚ / ‚ÄúUse Z‚ÄĚ</li>
  <li>ūüďĚ <strong>Draft changes</strong> ‚ÄĒ Edits to something we‚Äôre working on</li>
  <li>ūüĒĘ <strong>Specific values</strong> ‚ÄĒ Numbers, dates, IDs, URLs</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="the-protocol">The Protocol</h3>

<p><strong>If ANY of these appear:</strong></p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>STOP</strong> ‚ÄĒ Do not start composing your response</li>
  <li><strong>WRITE</strong> ‚ÄĒ Update SESSION-STATE.md with the detail</li>
  <li><strong>THEN</strong> ‚ÄĒ Respond to your human</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>The urge to respond is the enemy.</strong> The detail feels so clear in context that writing it down seems unnecessary. But context will vanish. Write first.</p>

<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Human says: "Use the blue theme, not red"

WRONG: "Got it, blue!" (seems obvious, why write it down?)
RIGHT: Write to SESSION-STATE.md: "Theme: blue (not red)" ‚Üí THEN respond
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="why-this-works">Why This Works</h3>

<p>The trigger is the human‚Äôs INPUT, not your memory. You don‚Äôt have to remember to check ‚ÄĒ the rule fires on what they say. Every correction, every name, every decision gets captured automatically.</p>

