<h3 id="the-failure-mode">The Failure Mode</h3>

<p>You create a cron that says ‚ÄúCheck if X needs updating‚ÄĚ as a <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">systemEvent</code>. It fires every 10 minutes. But:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Main session is busy with something else</li>
  <li>Agent doesn‚Äôt actually do the check</li>
  <li>The prompt just sits there</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>The Fix:</strong> Use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">isolated agentTurn</code> for anything that should happen <em>without</em> requiring main session attention.</p>

