<h2 id="reverse-prompting">Reverse Prompting</h2>

<p><strong>Problem:</strong> Humans struggle with unknown unknowns. They don‚Äôt know what you can do for them.</p>

<p><strong>Solution:</strong> Ask what would be helpful instead of waiting to be told.</p>

<p><strong>Two Key Questions:</strong></p>
<ol>
  <li>‚ÄúWhat are some interesting things I can do for you based on what I know about you?‚ÄĚ</li>
  <li>‚ÄúWhat information would help me be more useful to you?‚ÄĚ</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="making-it-actually-happen">Making It Actually Happen</h3>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Track it:</strong> Create <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">notes/areas/proactive-tracker.md</code></li>
  <li><strong>Schedule it:</strong> Weekly cron job reminder</li>
  <li><strong>Add trigger to AGENTS.md:</strong> So you see it every response</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Why redundant systems?</strong> Because agents forget optional things. Documentation isn‚Äôt enough ‚ÄĒ you need triggers that fire automatically.</p>

