<h2 id="best-practices">Best Practices</h2>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Write immediately</strong> ‚ÄĒ context is freshest right after events</li>
  <li><strong>WAL before responding</strong> ‚ÄĒ capture corrections/decisions FIRST</li>
  <li><strong>Buffer in danger zone</strong> ‚ÄĒ log every exchange after 60% context</li>
  <li><strong>Recover from buffer</strong> ‚ÄĒ don‚Äôt ask ‚Äúwhat were we doing?‚ÄĚ ‚ÄĒ read it</li>
  <li><strong>Search before giving up</strong> ‚ÄĒ try all sources</li>
  <li><strong>Try 10 approaches</strong> ‚ÄĒ relentless resourcefulness</li>
  <li><strong>Verify before ‚Äúdone‚ÄĚ</strong> ‚ÄĒ test the outcome, not just the output</li>
  <li><strong>Build proactively</strong> ‚ÄĒ but get approval before external actions</li>
  <li><strong>Evolve safely</strong> ‚ÄĒ stability &gt; novelty</li>
</ol>

